SENATE BILL NO. 1501
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR SCHROER.
6503S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 311.185, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof one new section relating to direct
shipment of alcoholic beverages.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 311.185, RSMo, is repealed and one new
2 section enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as section 311.185,
3 to read as follows:
1 311.185. 1. Notwithstanding any rule, law, or
2 regulation to the contrary, any person currently licensed in
3 this state [or any other state] as a wine manufacturer,
4 distilled spirits manufacturer, or retailer under this
5 chapter may apply for, and the supervisor of alcohol and
6 tobacco control may issue, a [wine] direct shipper license,
7 as provided in this section[, which allows a wine]. The
8 license shall allow such manufacturer or retailer to ship
9 [up to two cases of] wine [per month] or distilled spirits
10 produced or lawfully purchased by the licensee, up to
11 volumes authorized in this section, directly to:
12 (1) A resident of this state who is at least twenty-
13 one years of age, for such resident's personal use and not
14 for resale[. Before sending any shipment to a resident of
15 this state, the wine manufacturer shall first obtain a wine
16 direct shipper license as follows:]; or
